<CLR_EXEC>.llm_response: The explanation provided uses the LIME (Local Interpretable Model-agnostic Explanations) technique to highlight the most important words in the text that contributed to the AI system's outcome. In this case, the AI predicted the class "HLR" with a probability of 1.00. The highlighted words in the text, such as "notes" and "pass," indicate their significance in influencing this prediction. LIME helps in understanding which parts of the input data are most influential in the model's decision-making process. In the ISee Platform, we have an explainer named '/Text/LIME' that provides a similar feature influence explanation for text data. This explainer perturbs the input data samples to train a simple model that approximates the prediction for the given instance and similar ones. It displays a plot with the most important words for the given instance, showing both positive and negative contributions of each word to the predicted outcome. Users can try out this explainer to gain insights into their text classification models.
